# Demonstrates: C92, C93 — conditional composition and guard-local proof narrowing

# The guarded row is safe because the proof only exists inside the when-true branch.
# The conditional rows show Hull behavior for conditional expressions used as divisors.

precept ConditionalCompositionDemo

field Amount as number default 100 positive
field Divisor as number default 1
field UseFallback as boolean default false
field GuardedShare as number default 0
field ConditionalShare as number default 0
field ZeroShare as number default 0

state Active initial
state Done

event ComputeGuarded
event ComputeConditional
event ComputeZeroConditional

# SAFE: the guard proves Divisor > 0 only inside this row.
from Active on ComputeGuarded when Divisor > 0 -> set GuardedShare = Amount / Divisor -> transition Done
from Active on ComputeGuarded -> transition Done

# C93: one branch is safe (1), the other has no proof (Divisor), so the merged divisor is still unresolved.
# EXPECT: C93 | severity=error | match=exact | message=Divisor 'expression' has no compile-time nonzero proof. Consider adding a 'positive' constraint, 'rule expression != 0', or 'when expression != 0' guard. | line=28 | start=69 | end=105
from Active on ComputeConditional -> set ConditionalShare = Amount / (if UseFallback then Divisor else 1) -> transition Done

# C92: both branches are the literal 0, so the conditional divisor is provably zero.
# EXPECT: C92 | severity=error | match=exact | message=Division by zero: divisor 'expression' is provably zero. | line=32 | start=66 | end=96
from Active on ComputeZeroConditional -> set ZeroShare = Amount / (if UseFallback then 0 else 0) -> transition Done
